<TITLE> City of black banners </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Aug 15 (bdnews24.com)The country was observing National Mourning Day, with special tributes and programmes to slain independence leader Bangabandhu Sheikh Mujibur Rahman on Saturday, a grey overcast and rainy day. Hundreds of black banners and posters, with writings in white ink, were seen and Sheikh Mujib's historic speeches were played on loudspeakers around the capital. The writings on the banners called for the pending sentences of Bangabandhu's convicted killers to be carried out. Hundreds of Individuals and organisations, Awami League supporters among them, had been putting up banners, posters and erecting gates around the country in Bangabandhu's memory, since the start of the month. Free food was being served to the destitute by different groups in many areas as part of the day's programmes. bd
